<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911002-0092</DOCNO><DOCID>911002-0092.</DOCID><HL>   Dividend News:   Hollywood Park Firms   Approve Stock Split   After Reorganization</HL><DATE>10/02/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   HTRFZ</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>DIVIDENDS (DIV)REAL ESTATE INVESTMENTS (REA)</IN><NS>DIVIDENDS (DIV)RESTRUCTURINGS, RECAPITALIZATION (RCN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   HOLLYWOOD, Calif. -- Hollywood Park Operating Co. andHollywood Park Realty Enterprises Inc. said they approved astock split to be distributed after the companies' plannedreorganization Jan. 2 into a single company named HollywoodPark Inc.   The reorganization calls for shareholders of the sistercompanies, which are paired for trading, to receive oneadditional share of Hollywood Park Realty for every threeshares currently held. Hollywood Park Operating would becomea unit of Hollywood Park Realty.</LP><TEXT>   Subsequently, a 7-for-4 stock split in the form of a stockdividend will give shareholders three additional new sharesin the reorganized Hollywood Park for every four shares held.After the reorganization and stock split Hollywood Park willhave about 9.3 million shares outstanding.   &quot;The stock split will be a positive step for all of ourshareholders since it will increase the company's float andshould give us an opportunity to attract broader investorinterest,&quot; said R.D. Hubbard, chairman and chief executiveofficer of the sister companies. The reorganization will endHollywood Park Realty's status as a real estate investmenttrust. Hollywood Park Operating runs a thoroughbred racetrack owned by the trust.</TEXT></DOC>